modules.description: This module provides functions to enhance dependency tracking and compilation rules in OCamlbuild. It supports operations like propagating predicates to ocamldep, alternative cmxs linking, and tracking external dependencies for incremental rebuilds. It works with standard OCamlbuild artifacts like cmxa, cmxs, and source dependencies. Useful for projects needing precise control over compilation pipelines and external library interactions without full rebuilds.

This module constructs `.install` files for OPAM packages by translating OASIS build artifacts into installable items. It defines functions to declare libraries, objects, executables, and individual files with their installation targets and sections. Users can generate a complete install file by providing a package name and a list of these items.
